made (for a given number of gridpoints) if the interpolation is constructed so that it also
matches the marginal propensity to consume at the gridpoints. Differentiating (50) with
respect to a (and dropping policy function arguments for simplicity) yields a marginal
propensity to have consumed ca at each gridpoint:
