Arrows reflect the direction of the relationship; an arrowhead points to the larger of the two quantities
being compared. For example, the topmost arrow, pointing from Ã to Î“, indicates that Î“ > Ã .

Figure J.1 should be read as follows. The three nodes represent the values of the
absolute patience factor Ã, the growth factor for permanent income Î“, and the riskfree
interest factor R. The arrows between these quantities represent imposition of the labeled
condition. For example, the uppermost arrow, pointing from Ã to Î“, reflects imposition
of the PF-GIC condition. To make interpretation of the diagram easy, the mathematical

